tine, although there was renewed threat of war over Mosul in 1925-1926. These events are the subject of the majority of the documents contained in this volume. Those that comprise the final section of the book show the Mediterranean Fleet back to preparation for a major war, applying the lessons of World War One and studying how to make use of new weapons, aircraft carriers and aircraft.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aMaritime History. 7aHISTORY / Military / Naval.2bisacsh  aAdmiral Osmund de Beauvoir Brock.  aAdmiralty.  aBlack Sea.  aBolsheviks.  aConstantinople.  aMalta.  aMediterranean.  aNaval Aviation.  aRear Admiral Michael Culme-Seymour.  aRoyal Navy.  aRussia.  aSmyrna.  aThe Interwar Years.  aTurkey.  aVice Admiral Frederick Field.  aVice Admiral John De Robeck.  aVice Admiral Roger Keyes.  aVice Admiral Sydney Freemantle.1 aHalpen, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781315555614423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781315555614/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles